 üß† How AI Tools Were Used

During the final development of GoalTribe, I used AI tools (mainly ChatGPT) to help me understand, debug, and improve my Kotlin code.  
The AI was not used to build the entire project automatically‚Äîit acted as a tutor and reference tool.

Examples of Use
1. *Code Snippet Assistance*
   - I asked for examples of how to implement a Room database with WorkManager to sync data.
   - The AI produced sample code which I then studied, modified, and integrated into my own app.
   - I added my own comments and changed variable names to fit my project.

2. Debugging
   - When I had Firebase Authentication errors like ‚ÄúDEVELOPER_ERROR‚Äù or FCM registration issues, I asked the AI to explain possible causes.
   - It helped me locate missing configuration steps in the Google Cloud Console and fixed them successfully.

3. Documentation & ReadMe Structure
   - I used AI to structure this README, release notes, and write a clearer explanation of my features.

4. Language Support
   - I asked for translations of a few interface strings to isiZulu and Afrikaans.  
   - I then verified the translations myself and adjusted them for accuracy.

---

‚öôÔ∏è Ethical Use & Citations
- All AI-generated text and code snippets were reviewed, edited, and rewritten by me.
- The AI‚Äôs suggestions served only as a guide‚Äîfinal logic and debugging were completed manually in Android Studio.
- Any snippet used from AI was cited in this document, and all Firebase/Android code follows Google‚Äôs open documentation examples.

---

 üìö Reflection
Using AI made it easier to understand new concepts like WorkManager, FCM, and localization.  
It felt like having a tutor explain complicated code one line at a time.  
However, I learned the importance of reading the official docs and testing each change myself.  
The AI was most useful for *learning reasoning*, not for copying code blindly.
